obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (25571)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_67_00001_199373_1517807322617&sectionId=25571&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_67_00001_199373_1517807322617
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the National Council for`
  line `Teacher Education Act, 1993.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India ^1***.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^2 as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
  line
  line `^3[(4) Save as otherwise provided in this Act, the provisions of this Act shall apply to--`
  line
  line `(a) institutions;`
  line
  line `(b) students and teachers of the institutions;`
  line
  line `(c) schools imparting pre-primary, primary, upper primary, secondary or senior secondary`
  line `education and colleges providing senior secondary or intermediate education irrespective of the fact,`
  line `by whatever names they may be called; and`
  line
  line `(d) teachers for schools and colleges referred to in clause (c).]`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "except the State of Jammu and Kashmir" omitted by Act 34 of 2019, s. 95 and the Fifth Schedule (w.e.f. 31-10-`
  line `2019).`
  line
  line `2. 1st July, 1995, vide notification No. S.O. 620(E), dated 1st July, 1995, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II, sec. 3(ii).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 18 of 2011, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-6-2012).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (25572)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_67_00001_199373_1517807322617&sectionId=25572&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_67_00001_199373_1517807322617
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "appointed day" means the date of establishment of the National Council for Teacher`
  line `Education under sub-section (1) of section 3;`
  line
  line `(b) "Chairperson" means the Chairperson of the Council appointed under clause (a) of`
  line `sub-section (4) of section 3;`
  line
  line `(c) "Council" means the National Council for Teacher Education established under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 3;`
  line
  line `(d) "examining body" means a University, agency or authority to which an institution is affiliated`
  line `for conducting examinations in teacher education qualifications;`
  line
  line `(e) "institution" means an institution which offers courses or training in teacher education;`
  line
  line `^1[(ea) "local authority" means a Municipal Corporation, Municipal Committee, Municipal`
  line `Council, Zila Parishad, District Board or Nagar Panchayat or Panchayat, or other authority (by`
  line `whatever name called), legally entitled to, or entrusted by the Government with the control or`
  line `management of a municipal or local fund;]`
  line
  line `(f) "Member" means a Member of the Council and includes the Chairperson and`
  line Vice-Chairperson;
  line
  line `(g) "Member-Secretary" means the Member-Secretary of the Council appointed under clause (c)`
  line `of sub-section (4) of section 3;`
  line
  line `(h) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under section 31;`
  line
  line `(i) "recognised institution" means an institution recognised by the Council under section 14;`
  line
  line `(j) "Regional Committee" means a committee established under section 20;`
  line
  line `(k) "regulations" means regulations made under section 32;`
  line
  line `^2[(ka) "school" means any recognised school imparting pre-primary, primary, upper primary,`
  line `secondary or senior secondary education, or a college imparting senior secondary education, and`
  line includes--
  line
  line `(i) a school established, owned and controlled by the Central Government, or the State`
  line `Government or a local authority;`
  line
  line `(ii) a school receiving aid or grants to meet whole or part of its expenses from the Central`
  line `Government, the State Government or a local authority;`
  line
  line `(iii) a school not receiving any aid or grants to meet whole or part of its expenses from the`
  line `Central Government, the State Government or a local authority;]`
  line
  line `(l) "teacher education" means programmes of education, research or training of persons for`
  line `equipping them to teach at pre-primary, primary, secondary and senior secondary stages in schools,`
  line `and includes non-formal education, part-time education, adult education and correspondence`
  line education;
  line
  line `(m) "teacher education qualification" means a degree, diploma or certificate in teacher education`
  line `awarded by a University or examining body in accordance with the provisions of this Act;`
  line
  line `(n) "University" means a University defined under clause (f) of section 2 of the University Grants`
  line `Commission Act, 1956 (3 of 1956), and includes an institution deemed to be a University under`
  line `section 3 of that Act;`
  line
  line `(o) "Vice-Chairperson" means the Vice-Chairperson of the Council appointed under clause (b) of`
  line `sub-section (4) of section 3.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 . Ins. by s. 4, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-6-2012).`
  line
  line `2 Ins. by Act 18 of 2011, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-6-2012).`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (25573)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Establishment of the Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_67_00001_199373_1517807322617&sectionId=25573&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_67_00001_199373_1517807322617
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) With effect from such date as the Central Government may,`
  line `by notification in the Official Gazette, appoint, there shall be established a Council to be called the`
  line `National Council for Teacher Education.`
  line
  line `(2) The Council shall be a body corporate by the name aforesaid, having perpetual succession and a`
  line `common seal with power to contract and shall, by the said name, sue and be sued.`
  line
  line `(3) The head office of the Council shall be at Delhi and the Council may, with the previous approval`
  line `of the Central Government, establish regional offices at other places in India.`
  line
  line `(4) The Council shall consist of the following Members, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) a Chairperson to be appointed by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(b) a Vice-Chairperson to be appointed by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(c) a Member-Secretary to be appointed by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(d) the Secretary to the Government of India in the Department dealing with Education, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(e) the Chairman, University Grants Commission established under section 4 of the University`
  line `Grants Commission Act, 1956 (3 of 1956) or a member thereof nominated by him, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(f) the Director, National Council of Educational Research and Training, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(g) the Director, National Institute of Educational Planning and Administration, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(h) the Adviser (Education), Planning Commission, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(i) the Chairman, Central Board of Secondary Education, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(j) the Financial Adviser to the Government of India in the Department dealing with`
  line `Education, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(k) the Member-Secretary, All-India Council for Technical Education, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(l) the Chairpersons of all Regional Committees, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(m) thirteen persons possessing experience and knowledge in the field of education or teaching to`
  line `be appointed by the Central Government as under, from amongst the--`
  line
  line `(i) Deans of Faculties of Education and Professors of`
  line `Education in Universities`
  line --Four;
  line
  line `(ii) experts in secondary teacher education --One;`
  line
  line `(iii) experts in pre-primary and primary teacher education --Three;`
  line
  line `(iv) experts in non-formal education and adult education --Two;`
  line
  line `(v) experts in the field of natural sciences, social sciences,`
  line `linguistics, vocational education, work experience,`
  line `educational technology and special education, by rotation,`
  line `in the manner prescribed`
  line --Three;
  line
  line `(n) nine Members to be appointed by the Central Government to represent the States and Union`
  line `territory Administrations in the manner prescribed;`
  line
  line `(o) three Members of Parliament of whom one shall be nominated by the Chairman of the`
  line `Council of States and two by the Speaker of the House of the People;`
  line
  line `(p) three Members to be appointed by the Central Government from amongst teachers of primary`
  line `and secondary education and teachers of recognised institutions.`
  line
  line `(5) It is hereby declared that the office of the Member of the Council shall not disqualify its holder for`
  line `being chosen as or for being a member of either House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (25574)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Term of office and conditions of service of Members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_67_00001_199373_1517807322617&sectionId=25574&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_67_00001_199373_1517807322617
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chairperson, Vice-Chairperson`
  line `and the Member-Secretary shall hold office on a full-time basis.`
  line
  line `(2) The term of office of the Chairperson, the Vice-Chairperson and the Member-Secretary shall be`
  line `four years, or till they complete the age of sixty years, whichever is earlier.`
  line
  line `(3) The conditions of service of the Chairperson, the Vice-Chairperson and the Member-Secretary`
  line `shall be such as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) The term of office of Members other than the Members specified in clauses (a) to (l) and clauses`
  line `(n) and (o) of sub-section (4) of section 3 shall be two years or till fresh appointments are made,`
  line `whichever is later, and other conditions of service of such Members shall be such as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(5) If a casual vacancy occurs in the office of Chairperson, whether by reason of death, resignation or`
  line `inability to discharge the functions of a Chairperson owing to illness or other incapacity, the`
  line `Vice-Chairperson holding office as such for the time being, shall act as the Chairperson and shall, unless`
  line `any other person is appointed earlier as Chairperson, hold office of the Chairperson for the remainder of`
  line `the term of office of the person in whose place the said person is to so act.`
  line
  line `(6) If a casual vacancy occurs in the office of the Vice-Chairperson or any other Member, whether by`
  line `reason of death, resignation or inability to discharge his functions owing to illness or other incapacity, such vacancy shall be filled up by making fresh appointment and the person so appointed shall hold office`
  line `for the remainder of the term of the office of the person in whose place such person is so appointed.`
  line
  line `(7) The Chairperson shall, in addition to presiding over the meetings of the Council, exercise and`
  line `discharge such powers and duties of the Council as may be delegated to him by the Council and such`
  line `other powers and duties as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(8) The Vice-Chairperson shall perform such functions as may be assigned to him by the Chairperson`
  line `from time to time.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (25575)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Disqualification for office of Member.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_67_00001_199373_1517807322617&sectionId=25575&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_67_00001_199373_1517807322617
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `A person shall be disqualified for being appointed as a`
  line `Member if he--`
  line
  line `(a) has been convicted and sentenced to imprisonment for an offence, which, in the opinion of the`
  line `Central Government, involves moral turpitude; or`
  line
  line `(b) is an undischarged insolvent; or`
  line
  line `(c) is of unsound mind and stands so declared by a competent court; or`
  line
  line `(d) has been removed or dismissed from the service of the Government or a body corporate`
  line `owned or controlled by the Government; or`
  line
  line `(e) has in the opinion of the Central Government such financial or other interest in the Council as`
  line `is likely to affect prejudicially the discharge by him of his functions as a Member.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (25576)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Vacation of office of Member.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_67_00001_199373_1517807322617&sectionId=25576&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_67_00001_199373_1517807322617
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government shall remove a Member if he--`
  line
  line `(a) becomes subject to any of the disqualifications mentioned in section 5:`
  line
  line `Provided that no Member shall be removed on the ground that he has become subject to the`
  line `disqualification mentioned in clause (e) of that section, unless he has been given a reasonable`
  line `opportunity of being heard in the matter; or`
  line
  line `(b) refuses to act or becomes incapable of acting; or`
  line
  line `(c) is, without obtaining leave of absence from the Council, absent from three consecutive`
  line `meetings of the Council; or`
  line
  line `(d) in the opinion of the Central Government, has so abused his position as to render his`
  line `continuance in office detrimental to the public interest:`
  line
  line `Provided that no Member shall be removed under this clause unless he has been given a`
  line `reasonable opportunity of being heard in the matter.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (25577)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Meetings of the Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_67_00001_199373_1517807322617&sectionId=25577&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_67_00001_199373_1517807322617
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Council shall meet at such time and places, and shall observe`
  line `such rules of procedure in regard to the transaction of business at its meetings (including the quorum at`
  line `such meetings) as may be provided by regulations:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Council shall meet at least once every year.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chairperson, and in the absence of the Chairperson, the Vice-Chairperson shall preside at the`
  line `meetings of the Council.`
  line
  line `(3) If for any reason the Chairperson and the Vice-Chairperson, both are unable to attend any meeting`
  line `of the Council, any other Member chosen by the Members present at the meeting shall preside at that`
  line meeting.
  line
  line `(4) All questions which come up before any meeting of the Council shall be decided by a majority of`
  line `votes of the Members present and voting and in the event of any equality of votes, the Chairperson, or in`
  line `the absence of the Chairperson the person presiding, shall have and exercise a second or casting vote.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (25578)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Vacancies, etc., not to invalidate proceedings of the Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_67_00001_199373_1517807322617&sectionId=25578&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_67_00001_199373_1517807322617
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `No act or proceeding of the`
  line `Council shall be invalid merely by reason of--`
  line
  line `(a) any vacancy in, or any defect in the constitution of, the Council; or`
  line
  line `(b) any defect in the appointment of a person acting as a Member of the Council; or`
  line
  line `(c) any irregularity in the procedure of the Council not affecting the merits of the case.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (25579)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Power to co-opt.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_67_00001_199373_1517807322617&sectionId=25579&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_67_00001_199373_1517807322617
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Council may co-opt, in such manner and for such purposes as may be`
  line `determined by regulations, not more than three persons, whose assistance or advice it may desire in`
  line `carrying out any of the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The person co-opted by the Council under sub-section (1) for any purpose shall have a right to`
  line `take part in the discussions relevant to that purpose, but shall not have a right to vote at a meeting of the`
  line `Council, and shall not be a Member for any other purpose.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (25580)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Appointment of officers and other employees of the Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_67_00001_199373_1517807322617&sectionId=25580&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_67_00001_199373_1517807322617
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purpose of enabling`
  line `the Council to discharge its functions efficiently under this Act, the Council shall, subject to such`
  line `regulations as may be made in this behalf, appoint (whether on deputation or otherwise) such number of`
  line `officers and other employees as it may consider necessary:`
  line
  line `Provided that the category of posts equivalent to Group 'A' posts in the Central Government shall be`
  line `subject to the approval of the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) Every officer or other employee appointed by the Council shall be subject to such conditions of`
  line `service as may be determined by regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (25581)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Authentication of the orders and other instruments of the Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_67_00001_199373_1517807322617&sectionId=25581&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_67_00001_199373_1517807322617
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `All orders and decisions`
  line `of the Council shall be authenticated by the signature of the Chairperson or any other Member authorised`
  line `by the Council in this behalf, and all other instruments issued by the Council shall be authenticated by the`
  line `signature of the Member-Secretary or any other officer of the Council authorised in like manner in this`
  line `behalf by the Chairperson.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (25582)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Functions of the Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes `1. The words "in schools or" omitted by Act 18 of 2011, s. 5 (w.e.f. 1-6-2012).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_67_00001_199373_1517807322617&sectionId=25582&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_67_00001_199373_1517807322617
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `It shall be the duty of the Council to take all such steps as it may`
  line `think fit for ensuring planned and co-ordinated development of teacher education and for the`
  line `determination and maintenance of standards for teacher education and for the purposes of performing its`
  line `functions under this Act, the Council may--`
  line
  line `(a) undertake surveys and studies relating to various aspects of teacher education and publish the`
  line `result thereof;`
  line
  line `(b) make recommendations to the Central and State Government, Universities, University Grants`
  line `Commission and recognised institutions in the matter of preparation of suitable plans and`
  line `programmes in the field of teacher education;`
  line
  line `(c) co-ordinate and monitor teacher education and its development in the country;`
  line
  line `(d) lay down guidelines in respect of minimum qualifications for a person to be employed as a`
  line `teacher ^1*** in recognised institutions;`
  line
  line `(e) lay down norms for any specified category of courses or trainings in teacher education,`
  line `including the minimum eligibility criteria for admission thereof, and the method of selection of`
  line `candidates, duration of the course, course contents and mode of curriculum;`
  line
  line `(f) lay down guidelines for compliance by recognised institutions, for starting new courses or`
  line `training, and for providing physical and instructional facilities, staffing pattern and staff qualification;`
  line
  line `(g) lay down standards in respect of examinations leading to teacher education qualifications,`
  line `criteria for admission to such examinations and schemes of courses or training;`
  line
  line `(h) lay down guidelines regarding tuition fees and other fees chargeable by recognised`
  line institutions;
  line
  line `(i) promote and conduct innovation and research in various areas of teacher education and`
  line `disseminate the results thereof;`
  line
  line `(j) examine and review periodically the implementation of the norms, guidelines and standards`
  line `laid down by the Council, and to suitably advise the recognised institutions;`
  line
  line `(k) evolve suitable performance appraisal system, norms and mechanisms for enforcing`
  line `accountability on recognised institutions;`
  line
  line `(l) formulate schemes for various levels of teacher education and identify recognised institutions`
  line `and set up new institutions for teacher development programmes;`
  line
  line `(m) take all necessary steps to prevent commercialisation of teacher education; and`
  line
  line `(n) perform such other functions as may be entrusted to it by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_a:
  sectionId (25583)
  sectionNo 12A
  orderNo 13
  title `Power of Council to determine minimum standards of education of school teachers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_a_content
  footnotes `1 Ins. by Act 18 of 2011, s. 6 (w.e.f. 1-6-2012).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_67_00001_199373_1517807322617&sectionId=25583&sectionno=12A&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_67_00001_199373_1517807322617
obj_root_law_sections_12_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[12A. Power of Council to determine minimum standards of education of school teachers. -- For`
  line `the purpose of maintaining standards of education in schools, the Council may, by regulations, determine`
  line `the qualifications of persons for being recruited as teachers in any pre-primary, primary, upper primary,`
  line `secondary, senior secondary or intermediate school or college, by whatever name called, established, run,`
  line `aided or recognised by the Central Government or a State Government or a local or other authority:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this section shall adversely affect the continuance of any person recruited in`
  line `any pre-primary, primary, upper primary, secondary, senior secondary or intermediate schools or`
  line `colleges, under any rule, regulation or order made by the Central Government, a State Government, a`
  line `local or other authority, immediately before the commencement of the National Council for Teacher`
  line `Education (Amendment) Act, 2011 (18 of 2011) solely on the ground of non-fulfilment of such`
  line `qualifications as may be specified by the Council:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the minimum qualifications of a teacher referred to in the first proviso shall be`
  line `acquired within the period specified in this Act or under the Right of Children to Free and Compulsory`
  line `Education Act, 2009 (35 of 2009).]`
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (25584)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 14
  title Inspection.
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_67_00001_199373_1517807322617&sectionId=25584&sectionno=13&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_67_00001_199373_1517807322617
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purpose of ascertaining whether the recognised institutions are`
  line `functioning in accordance with the provisions of this Act, the Council may cause inspection of any such`
  line `institution, to be made by such persons as it may direct, and in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The Council shall communicate to the institution the date on which inspection under`
  line `sub-section (1) is to be made and the institution shall be entitled to be associated with the inspection in`
  line `such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) The Council shall communicate to the said institution, its views in regard to the results of any such`
  line `inspection and may, after ascertaining the opinion of that institution, recommend to that institution the`
  line `action to be taken as a result of such inspection.`
  line
  line `(4) All communications to the institution under this section shall be made to the executive authority`
  line `thereof, and the executive authority of the institution shall report to the Council the action, if any, which`
  line `is proposed to be taken for the purpose of implementing any such recommendation as is referred to in`
  line `sub-section (3).`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (25585)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 15
  title `Recognition of institutions offering course or training in teacher education.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes `1. The proviso ins. by Act 2 of 2019, s. 2 (w.e.f. 17.08.1995).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_67_00001_199373_1517807322617&sectionId=25585&sectionno=14&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_67_00001_199373_1517807322617
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every`
  line `institution offering or intending to offer a course or training in teacher education on or after the appointed`
  line `day, may, for grant of recognition under this Act, make an application to the Regional Committee`
  line `concerned in such form and in such manner as may be determined by regulations:`
  line
  line `Provided that an institution offering a course or training in teacher education immediately before the`
  line `appointed day, shall be entitled to continue such course or training for a period of six months, if it has`
  line `made an application for recognition within the said period and until the disposal of the application by the`
  line `Regional Committee.`
  line
  line `^1[Provided further that such institutions, as may be specified by the Central Government by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, which--`
  line
  line `(i) are funded by the Central Government or the State Government or the Union territory`
  line Administration;
  line
  line `(ii) have offered a course or training in teacher education on or after the appointed day till the`
  line `academic year 2017-2018; and`
  line
  line `(iii) fulfil the conditions specified under clause (a) of sub-section (3),`
  line
  line `shall be deemed to have been recognised by the Regional Committee.]`
  line
  line `(2) The fee to be paid along with the application under sub-section (1) shall be such as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `(3) On receipt of an application by the Regional Committee from any institution under`
  line `sub-section (1), and after obtaining from the institution concerned such other particulars as it may`
  line `consider necessary, it shall,--`
  line
  line `(a) if it is satisfied that such institution has adequate financial resources, accommodation, library,`
  line `qualified staff, laboratory and that it fulfils such other conditions required for proper functioning of`
  line `the institution for a course or training in teacher education, as may be determined by regulations, pass`
  line `an order granting recognition to such institution, subject to such conditions as may be determined by`
  line `regulations; or`
  line
  line `(b) if it is of the opinion that such institution does not fulfil the requirements laid down in`
  line `sub-clause (a), pass an order refusing recognition to such institution for reasons to be recorded in`
  line `writing:`
  line
  line `Provided that before passing an order under sub-clause (b), the Regional Committee shall provide a`
  line `reasonable opportunity to the concerned institution for making a written representation.`
  line
  line `(4) Every order granting or refusing recognition to an institution for a course or training in teacher`
  line `education under sub-section (3) shall be published in the Official Gazette and communicated in writing`
  line `for appropriate action to such institution and to the concerned examining body, the local authority or the`
  line `State Government and the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(5) Every institution, in respect of which recognition has been refused shall discontinue the course or`
  line `training in teacher education from the end of the academic session next following the date of receipt of`
  line `the order refusing recognition passed under clause (b) of sub-section (3).`
  line
  line `(6) Every examining body shall, on receipt of the order under sub-section (4),--`
  line
  line `(a) grant affiliation to the institution, where recognition has been granted; or`
  line
  line `(b) cancel the affiliation of the institution, where recognition has been refused.`
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (25586)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 16
  title `Permission for a new course or training by recognised institution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes `1. The proviso ins. by s. 3, ibid. (w.e.f. 17.08.1995).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_67_00001_199373_1517807322617&sectionId=25586&sectionno=15&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_67_00001_199373_1517807322617
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any recognised`
  line `institution intends to start any new course or training in teacher education, it may make an application to`
  line `seek permission therefor to the Regional Committee concerned in such form and in such manner as may`
  line `be determined by regulations.`
  line
  line `^1[Provided that the course or training in teacher education offered on or after the appointed day till the`
  line `academic year 2017-2018 by such institutions, as may be specified by the Central Government by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, which--`
  line
  line `(i) are funded by the Central Government or the State Government or the Union territory`
  line `Administration; and`
  line
  line `(ii) fulfil the conditions specified under clause (a) of sub-section (3),`
  line
  line `shall be deemed to have been granted permission by the Regional Committee.]`
  line
  line `(2) The fees to be paid along with the application under sub-section (1) shall be such as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `(3) On receipt of an application from an institution under sub-section (1), and after obtaining from the`
  line `recognised institution such other particulars as may be considered necessary, the Regional Committee`
  line shall,--
  line
  line `(a) if it is satisfied that such recognised institution has adequate financial resources,`
  line `accommodation, library, qualified staff, laboratory, and that it fulfils such other conditions required`
  line `for proper conduct of the new course or training in teacher education, as may be determined by`
  line `regulations, pass an order granting permission, subject to such conditions as may be determined by`
  line `regulations; or`
  line
  line `(b) if it is of the opinion that such institution does not fulfil the requirements laid down in`
  line `sub-clause (a), pass an order refusing permission to such institution for reasons to be recorded in`
  line `writing:`
  line
  line `Provided that before passing an order refusing permission under sub-class (b), the Regional`
  line `Committee shall provide a reasonable opportunity to the institution concerned for making a written`
  line representation.
  line
  line `(4) Every order granting or refusing permission to a recognised institution for a new course or`
  line `training in teacher education under sub-section (3), shall be published in the Official Gazette and`
  line `communicated in writing for appropriate action to such recognised institution and to the concerned`
  line `examining body, the local authority, the State Government and the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (25587)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 17
  title `Affiliating body to grant affiliation after recognition or permission by the Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_67_00001_199373_1517807322617&sectionId=25587&sectionno=16&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_67_00001_199373_1517807322617
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force, no examining body`
  line `shall, on or after the appointed day,--`
  line
  line `(a) grant affiliation, whether provisional or otherwise, to any institution; or`
  line
  line `(b) hold examination, whether provisional or otherwise, for a course or training conducted by a`
  line `recognised institution,`
  line `unless the institution concerned has obtained recognition from the Regional Committee concerned, under`
  line `section 14 or permission for a course or training under section 15.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (25588)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 18
  title `Contravention of provisions of the Act and consequences thereof.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_67_00001_199373_1517807322617&sectionId=25588&sectionno=17&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_67_00001_199373_1517807322617
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the Regional`
  line `Committee is, on its own motion or on any representation received from any person, satisfied that a`
  line `recognised institution has contravened any of the provisions of this Act, or the rules, regulations, orders`
  line `made or issued thereunder, or any condition subject to which recognition under sub-section (3) of`
  line `section 14 or permission under sub-section (3) of section 15 was granted, it may withdraw recognition of`
  line `such recognised institution, for reasons to be recorded in writing:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order against the recognised institution shall be passed unless a reasonable`
  line `opportunity of making representation against the proposed order has been given to such recognised`
  line `institution:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the order withdrawing or refusing recognition passed by the Regional`
  line `Committee shall come into force only with effect from the end of the academic session next following the`
  line `date of communication of such order.`
  line
  line `(2) A copy of every order passed by the Regional Committee under sub-section (1),--`
  line
  line `(a) shall be communicated to the recognised institution concerned and a copy thereof shall also be`
  line `forwarded simultaneously to the University or the examining body to which such institution was`
  line `affiliated for cancelling affiliation; and--`
  line
  line `(b) shall be published in the Official Gazette for general information.`
  line
  line `(3) Once the recognition of a recognised institution is withdrawn under sub-section (1), such`
  line `institution shall discontinue the course or training in teacher education, and the concerned University or`
  line `the examining body shall cancel affiliation of the institution in accordance with the order passed under`
  line `sub-section (1), with effect from the end of the academic session next following the date of`
  line `communication of the said order.`
  line
  line `(4) If an institution offers any course or training in teacher education after the coming into force of`
  line `the order withdrawing recognition under sub-section (1), or where an institution offering a course or`
  line `training in teacher education immediately before the appointed day fails or neglects to obtain recognition`
  line `or permission under this Act, the qualification in teacher education obtained pursuant to such course or`
  line `training or after undertaking a course or training in such institution, shall not be treated as a valid`
  line `qualification for purposes of employment under the Central Government, any State Government or`
  line `University, or in any school, college or other educational body aided by the Central Government or any`
  line `State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (25589)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 19
  title Appeals.
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_67_00001_199373_1517807322617&sectionId=25589&sectionno=18&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_67_00001_199373_1517807322617
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person aggrieved by an order made under section 14 or section 15 or`
  line `section 17 of the Act may prefer an appeal to the Council within such period as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) No appeal shall be admitted if it is preferred after the expiry of the period prescribed therefor:`
  line
  line `Provided that an appeal may be admitted after the expiry of the period prescribed therefor, if the`
  line `appellant satisfies the Council that he had sufficient cause for not preferring the appeal within the`
  line `prescribed period.`
  line
  line `(3) Every appeal made under this section shall be made in such form and shall be accompanied by a`
  line `copy of the order appealed against and by such fees as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) The procedure for disposing of an appeal shall be such as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that before disallowing an appeal, the appellant shall be given a reasonable opportunity to`
  line `represent its case.`
  line
  line `(5) The Council may confirm or reverse the order appealed against.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (25590)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 20
  title `Executive Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_67_00001_199373_1517807322617&sectionId=25590&sectionno=19&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_67_00001_199373_1517807322617
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Council shall constitute a Committee, called Executive`
  line `Committee for discharging such functions as may be assigned to it by the Council or as may be`
  line `determined by regulations.`
  line
  line `(2) The Executive Committee shall consist of the following members, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the Chairperson;`
  line
  line `(b) the Vice-Chairperson;`
  line
  line `(c) the Member-Secretary;`
  line
  line `(d) the Secretary to the Government of India in the Department dealing with`
  line `Education, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(e) the Secretary, University Grants Commission, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(f) the Director, National Council of Educational Research and Training, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(g) the Financial Adviser to the Government of India in the Department dealing with`
  line `Education, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(h) four experts in teacher education to be nominated by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(i) four State representatives to be nominated by the Central Government in such manner as may`
  line `be prescribed;`
  line
  line `(j) the Chairpersons of the Regional Committees.`
  line
  line `(3) The Chairperson and the Member-Secretary of the Council shall respectively, function as the`
  line `Chairperson and the Member-Secretary of the Executive Committee.`
  line
  line `(4) The Chairperson or in his absence, the Vice-Chairperson of the Council shall preside at the`
  line `meetings of the Executive Committee and in the absence of both the Chairperson and the`
  line `Vice-Chairperson, any other member chosen by the members present at the meeting shall preside at the`
  line meeting.
  line
  line `(5) The quorum necessary for the transaction of business at the meetings of the Executive Committee`
  line `shall be as laid down by regulations.`
  line
  line `(6) The Executive Committee may co-opt, in such manner and for such purposes, as may be`
  line `determined by regulations, not more than two persons whose assistance and advice, it may desire in`
  line `carrying out any of the functions assigned to the Executive Committee:`
  line
  line `Provided that the persons co-opted by the Executive Committee for any purpose shall have a right to`
  line `take part in the discussions relevant to that purpose, but shall not have a right to vote at a meeting of the`
  line `Executive Committee, and shall not be a member for any other purpose.`
  line
  line `(7) The Council may, if it considers necessary, establish such other committees, for such specific`
  line `purpose, as it may deem fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (25591)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 21
  title `Regional Committees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_67_00001_199373_1517807322617&sectionId=25591&sectionno=20&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_67_00001_199373_1517807322617
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Council shall, by notification in the Official Gazette, establish`
  line `the following Regional Committees, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) the Eastern Regional Committee;`
  line
  line `(ii) the Western Regional Committee;`
  line
  line `(iii) the Northern Regional Committee; and`
  line
  line `(iv) the Southern Regional Committee.`
  line
  line `(2) The Council may, if it considers necessary, establish with the approval of the Central`
  line `Government, such other Regional Committees as it may deem fit.`
  line
  line `(3) The Regional Committee shall consist of the following members, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) a Member to be nominated by the Council;`
  line
  line `(b) one representative from each of the States and the Union territories of the region, to be`
  line `nominated by the respective States and the Union territories;`
  line
  line `(c) such number of persons, having special knowledge and experience in matters relating to`
  line `teacher education, as may be determined by regulations.`
  line
  line `(4) The Council shall nominate one of the members of the concerned Regional Committee to function`
  line `as the chairperson of the said Committee.`
  line
  line `(5) The term of office of the members referred to in clause (c) and the allowances payable to such`
  line `members shall be such as may be determined by regulations.`
  line
  line `(6) The Regional Committee shall, in addition to its functions under sections 14, 15 and 17, perform`
  line `such other functions, as may be assigned to it by the Council or as may be determined by regulations.`
  line
  line `(7) The functions of, the procedure to the followed by, the territorial jurisdiction of, and the manner`
  line `of filling casual vacancies among members of, a Regional Committee shall be such as may be determined`
  line `by regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (25592)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 22
  title `Power to terminate the Regional Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_67_00001_199373_1517807322617&sectionId=25592&sectionno=21&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_67_00001_199373_1517807322617
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the Council is of the opinion that a`
  line `Regional Committee is unable to perform, or has persistently made default in the performance of the`
  line `duties imposed on it by or under this Act or has exceeded or abused its powers, or has wilfully or without`
  line `sufficient cause, failed to comply with any direction issued by the Council for carrying out the provisions`
  line `of this Act, the Council may, by notification in the Official Gazette, terminate forthwith the Regional`
  line Committee.
  line
  line `(2) Upon the publication of a notification under sub-section (1),--`
  line
  line `(a) all members of the Regional Committee shall, notwithstanding that their term of office had`
  line `not expired, as from the date of the termination, vacate their office as such members; and`
  line
  line `(b) all the powers and duties which may, by or under the provisions of this Act be exercised or`
  line `performed by or on behalf of the Regional Committee shall, during the period when the term of office`
  line `of its members stand terminated, be exercised and performed by such person or persons as the`
  line `Council may direct.`
  line
  line `(3) The Council may at any time after publication of a notification under sub-section (2), re-constitute`
  line `the Regional Committee in the manner provided in sub-section (3) of section 20:`
  line
  line `Provided that it shall be competent for the Council to appoint any person, who was a member of a`
  line `Regional Committee which was terminated, as a member of the reconstituted Regional Committee.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (25593)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 23
  title `Payment to the Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_67_00001_199373_1517807322617&sectionId=25593&sectionno=22&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_67_00001_199373_1517807322617
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, after due appropriation made by`
  line `Parliament by law in this behalf, pay to the Council in each financial year such sums as may be`
  line `considered necessary for the performance of the functions of the Council under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (25594)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 24
  title `Fund of the Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_67_00001_199373_1517807322617&sectionId=25594&sectionno=23&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_67_00001_199373_1517807322617
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Council shall have its own fund; and all sums which may, from`
  line `time to time, be paid to it by the Central Government or a State Government and all the receipts of the`
  line `Council, including any sum which any other authority or person in India or abroad may pay to the`
  line `Council, shall be credited to the fund and all payments by the Council shall be made therefrom.`
  line
  line `(2) All moneys belonging to the fund shall be deposited in such banks or invested in such manner as`
  line `may be decided by the Council.`
  line
  line `(3) The Council may spend such sums as it thinks fit for performing its functions under this Act, and`
  line `such sums shall be treated as expenditure payable out of the fund of the Council.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (25595)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 25
  title `Budget of the Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_67_00001_199373_1517807322617&sectionId=25595&sectionno=24&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_67_00001_199373_1517807322617
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `The Council shall prepare, in such form and at such time each year as`
  line `may be prescribed, a budget in respect of the financial year next ensuing, showing the estimated receipts`
  line `and expenditure, and copies thereof shall be forwarded to the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (25596)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 26
  title `Annual report.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_67_00001_199373_1517807322617&sectionId=25596&sectionno=25&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_67_00001_199373_1517807322617
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `The Council shall prepare once every year, in such form and at such time as`
  line `may be prescribed, an annual report giving a true and full account of its activities during the previous year`
  line `and copies thereof shall be forwarded to the Central Government and that Government shall cause the`
  line `same to be laid before both Houses of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (25597)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 27
  title `Accounts and audit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_67_00001_199373_1517807322617&sectionId=25597&sectionno=26&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_67_00001_199373_1517807322617
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Council shall cause to be maintained such books of account in`
  line `such form and in such manner and as the Central Government may, in consultation with the Comptroller`
  line `and Auditor-General of India, prescribe.`
  line
  line `(2) The Council shall, as soon as may be, after closing its annual accounts, prepare a statement of`
  line `accounts in such form and forward the same to the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India by such date`
  line `as the Central Government may, in consultation with the Comptroller and Auditor-General, determine.`
  line
  line `(3) The accounts of the Council shall be audited by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India at`
  line `such times and in such manner as he think fit.`
  line
  line `(4) The accounts of the Council as certified by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India or any`
  line `other person appointed by him in this behalf, together with the audit report thereon shall be forwarded`
  line `annually to the Central Government and that Government shall cause the same to be laid before both`
  line `Houses of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (25598)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 28
  title `Delegation of powers and functions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_67_00001_199373_1517807322617&sectionId=25598&sectionno=27&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_67_00001_199373_1517807322617
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `The Council may, by general or special order in writing,`
  line `delegate to the chairperson or to any other member or to any officer of the Regional Committee, subject`
  line `to such conditions and limitations, if any, as may be specified in the order, such of its powers and`
  line `functions under this Act (except the power to make regulations under section 32), as it may deem`
  line necessary.
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (25599)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 29
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_67_00001_199373_1517807322617&sectionId=25599&sectionno=28&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_67_00001_199373_1517807322617
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `No prosecution or other legal proceeding shall lie`
  line `against the Central Government, the Council or any committees appointed by it, or any Member of the`
  line `Council or member of such committees, or any officer or employee of the Central Government or the`
  line `Council or any other person authorised by that Government or the Council, for anything which is in good`
  line `faith done or intended to be done under this Act or the rules or regulations made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (25600)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 30
  title `Directions by the Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_67_00001_199373_1517807322617&sectionId=25600&sectionno=29&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_67_00001_199373_1517807322617
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Council shall, in the discharge of its functions`
  line `and duties under this Act be bound by such directions on questions of policy as the Central Government`
  line `may give in writing to it from time to time.`
  line
  line `(2) The decision of the Central Government as to whether a question is one of policy or not shall be`
  line final.
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (25601)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 31
  title `Power to supersede the Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_67_00001_199373_1517807322617&sectionId=25601&sectionno=30&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_67_00001_199373_1517807322617
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the Central Government is of the opinion that the`
  line `Council is unable to perform, or has persistently made default in the performance of the duties imposed`
  line `on it by or under this Act or has exceeded or abused its power, or has wilfully or without sufficient cause`
  line `failed to comply with any direction issued by the Central Government under section 29, the Central`
  line `Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, supersede the Council for such period as may be`
  line `specified in the notification:`
  line
  line `Provided that before issuing a notification under this sub-section, the Central Government shall give`
  line `reasonable opportunity to the Council to show cause why it should not be superseded and shall consider`
  line `the explanation and objections, if any, of the Council.`
  line
  line `(2) Upon the publication of a notification under sub-section (1) superseding the Council--`
  line
  line `(a) all the Members of the Council shall, notwithstanding that their term of office had not expired,`
  line `as from the date of supersession, vacate their offices as such Members;`
  line
  line `(b) all the powers and duties which may, by or under the provisions of this Act be exercised or`
  line `performed by or on behalf of the Council shall, during the period of supersession, be exercised and`
  line `performed by such person or persons as the Central Government may direct;`
  line
  line `(c) all property vested in the Council shall, during the period of supersession, vest in the Central`
  line Government.
  line
  line `(3) On the expiry of the period of supersession specified in the notification issued under`
  line `sub-section (1), the Central Government, may--`
  line
  line `(a) extend the period of supersession for such further period as it may consider necessary; or`
  line
  line `(b) reconstitute the Council in the manner provided in section 3.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (25602)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 32
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_67_00001_199373_1517807322617&sectionId=25602&sectionno=31&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_67_00001_199373_1517807322617
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules to carry out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing powers, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the manner in which Central Government is to appoint experts to the Council under`
  line `sub-clause (v) of clause (m) of sub-section (4) of section 3;`
  line
  line `(b) the manner in which the Central Government is to appoint Members to the Council from`
  line `amongst the States and the Union territory Administrations under clause (n) of sub-section (4) of`
  line `section 3;`
  line
  line `(c) the conditions of service of the Chairperson, the Vice-Chairperson and the Member-Secretary`
  line `under sub-section (3) and of Members under sub-section (4) of section 4;`
  line
  line `(d) the powers and duties of the Chairperson under sub-section (7) of section 4;`
  line
  line `(e) the manner in which and the persons by whom the inspection of an institution is to be made`
  line `and the manner in which the institution is to be associated in such inspection under sub-sections (1)`
  line `and (2) of section 13;`
  line
  line `(f) the fees payable on application for obtaining recognition under sub-section (2) of section 14`
  line `and for obtaining permission under sub-section (2) of section 15;`
  line
  line `(g) the period of limitation for an appeal under sub-section (1) of section 18, the form in which`
  line `such appeal is to be made and the fees payable therefor under sub-section (3) of that section and the`
  line `procedure for disposal of an appeal under sub-section (4) of that section;`
  line
  line `(h) the manner in which the Central Government is to nominate the State representatives in the`
  line `Executive Committee under clause (i) of sub-section (2) of section 19;`
  line
  line `(i) the form in which and the time within which the budget under section 24 and the annual report`
  line `under section 25 of the Council is to be prepared;`
  line
  line `(j) the manner and the form in which the accounts of the Council are to be maintained under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 26;`
  line
  line `(k) any other matter which has to be, or may be, prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (25603)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 33
  title `Power to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes `1 Ins. by Act 18 of 2011, s. 7 (w.e.f. 1-6-2012).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_67_00001_199373_1517807322617&sectionId=25603&sectionno=32&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_67_00001_199373_1517807322617
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Council may, by notification in the Official Gazette, make`
  line `regulations not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act and the rules made thereunder, generally to`
  line `carry out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such regulations may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the time and the place of the meetings of the Council and the procedure for conducting`
  line `business thereat under sub-section (1) of section 7;`
  line
  line `(b) the manner in which and the purposes for which persons may be co-opted by the Council`
  line `under sub-section (1) of section 9;`
  line
  line `(c) the appointment and terms and conditions of service of officers and other employees of the`
  line `Council under sub-sections (1) and (2) respectively of section 10;`
  line
  line `(d) the norms, guidelines and standards in respect of--`
  line
  line `(i) the minimum qualifications for a person to be employed as a teacher under clause (d) of`
  line `section 12;`
  line
  line `(ii) the specified category of courses or training in teacher education under clause (e) of`
  line `section 12;`
  line
  line `(iii) starting of new courses or training in recognised institutions under clause (f) of`
  line `section 12;`
  line
  line `(iv) standards in respect of examinations leading to teacher education qualifications referred`
  line `to in clause (g) of section 12;`
  line
  line `(v) the tuition fees and other fees chargeable by institutions under clause (h) of section 12;`
  line
  line `(vi) the schemes for various levels of teacher education, and identification of institutions for`
  line `offering teacher development programmes under clause (l) of section 12;`
  line
  line `^1[(dd) the qualifications of teachers under section 12A;]`
  line
  line `(e) the form and the manner in which an application for recognition is to be submitted under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 14;`
  line
  line `(f) conditions required for the proper functioning of the institution and conditions for granting`
  line `recognition under clause (a) of sub-section (3) of section 14;`
  line
  line `(g) the form and the manner in which an application for permission is to be made under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 15;`
  line
  line `(h) conditions required for the proper conduct of a new course or training and conditions for`
  line `granting permission under clause (a) of sub-section (3) of section 15;`
  line
  line `(i) the functions which may be assigned by the Council to the Executive Committee under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 19;`
  line
  line `(j) the procedure and the quorum necessary for transaction of business at the meetings of the`
  line `Executive Committee under sub-section (5) of section 19;`
  line
  line `(k) the manner in which and the purposes for which the Executive Committee may co-opt persons`
  line `under sub-section (6) of section 19;`
  line
  line `(l) the number of persons under clause (c) of sub-section (3) of section 20;`
  line
  line `(m) the term of office and allowances payable to members under sub-section (5) of section 20;`
  line
  line `(n) additional functions to be performed by the Regional Committee under sub-section (6) of`
  line `section 20;`
  line
  line `(o) the functions of, the procedure to be followed by, the territorial jurisdiction of, and the manner`
  line `of filling casual vacancies among members of, a Regional Committee under sub-section (7) of`
  line `section 20;`
  line
  line `(p) any other matter in respect of which provision is to be, or may be, made by regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (25604)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 34
  title `Rules and regulations to be laid before Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_67_00001_199373_1517807322617&sectionId=25604&sectionno=33&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_67_00001_199373_1517807322617
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `Every rule and every regulation made`
  line `under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it`
  line `is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one session or in two or more`
  line `successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately following the session or the`
  line `successive sessions aforesaid, both House agree in making any modification in the rule or regulation, or`
  line `both House agree that the rule or regulation should not be made, the rule or regulation shall thereafter`
  line `have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such`
  line `modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under`
  line `that rule or regulation.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (25605)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 35
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_67_00001_199373_1517807322617&sectionId=25605&sectionno=34&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_67_00001_199373_1517807322617
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, the Central Government may, by order, published in the Official Gazette, make such provisions`
  line `not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act as may appear to be necessary for removing the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no order shall be made under this section after the expiry of two years from the`
  line `commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
